# Laapak PO - Project Setup Walkthrough

## Overview
Successfully initialized and configured the Laapak PO application. This is a Next.js-based web application that allows Laapak staff to create professional Price Offers (POs) for B2B clients.

## What Was Built

### 1. Project Initialization
*   **Framework**: Next.js 16 with App Router
*   **Language**: TypeScript
*   **Styling**: Tailwind CSS 4
*   **Database**: MySQL via Prisma ORM

### 2. Database Schema
Created four core models in [schema.prisma](file:///media/saif/brain/Projects/Laapak%20PO/laapak-po-web/prisma/schema.prisma):

*   **Client**: Represents companies (the "folders" concept)
*   **PurchaseOffer**: The PO documents with status tracking
*   **LineItem**: Product details within each PO
*   **POView**: Analytics for tracking when clients open POs

### 3. Core Utilities
Created [utils.ts](file:///media/saif/brain/Projects/Laapak%20PO/laapak-po-web/src/lib/utils.ts) with:
*   [cn()](file:///media/saif/brain/Projects/Laapak%20PO/laapak-po-web/src/lib/utils.ts#4-7) - Tailwind class merging
*   [generatePublicId()](file:///media/saif/brain/Projects/Laapak%20PO/laapak-po-web/src/lib/utils.ts#8-20) - Secure 8-character ID generator (e.g., `x7k9-m2p4`)
*   [formatCurrency()](file:///media/saif/brain/Projects/Laapak%20PO/laapak-po-web/src/lib/utils.ts#21-27) - International currency formatting

### 4. Dashboard UI
Built the initial dashboard in [page.tsx](file:///media/saif/brain/Projects/Laapak%20PO/laapak-po-web/src/app/page.tsx):
*   Clean header with Laapak branding
*   Grid view of clients (empty state shown when no clients exist)
*   "New Client" action button

## Database Configuration

**Connection String**:
```
mysql://laapak:laapaksql@localhost:3306/laapak_po
```

**Prisma Version**: Downgraded to **Prisma 6** due to compatibility issues with Prisma 7's adapter requirement in Next.js 16.

**Applied Schema**: All 4 tables created successfully using `prisma db push`.

